snippet: Trading was quiet ahead of the jobs data, which may influence the Fed’s strategy on interest rates. Nonfarm payrolls are expected to rise by 200,000.
abstract: Stocks remain mostly unchanged as oil price rally faded and investors waited for April jobs report.

headline.main: Wall Street Ends Close to Even as It Looks to Friday’s Jobs Report
headline.print_headline: Wall Street Ends Close to Where It Started
